<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Sees World's Highest Death Rate Among Smokers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Thirty percent of Kazak adults
are smokers and their death rate is the highest in the world, a
report released by the World Health Organization (WHO) here said
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
About 60 percent of Kazak college students are smokers, the
report said, while the percentage in middle schools is even
higher, at 70 percent.
</P>
<P>
WHO statistics also showed that Denmark has the second highest
percentage of deaths related to smoking.
</P>
<P>
The report was made public at an on-going international
conference here sponsored by the WHO on the policy of smoking and
drinking. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
