<DOCNO> XIE19980404.0004 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Jones Industrial Average Crosses 9,000 For First Time </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
briefly moved above 9,000 in the New York stock market for the first
time in history.
</P>
<P>
The Dow was up 15.95 points at 9,002.59 in the opening minutes of
trading. As it reached its high, cheers and applause rose from the
floor of the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
But the Dow quickly slipped back to below the close of 8,986.64
on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average has been rising in recent weeks.
</P>
<P>
The move above 9,000 brings the stock market's gain this year to 14
percent, above some of the most optimistic forecasts for the full
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
