<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Basic Law Means Hong Kong-Mainland Ties Entering New Era (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Secretary for Constitutional
Affairs, Michael Suen, told a symposium on Friday that relations
between the Chinese mainland and Hong Kong entered a new era
after Hong Kong was returned to China on July 1 last year.
</P>
<P>
He told the symposium, "Hong Kong is Our Home", which was held
on the occasion of the eighth anniversary of the Basic Law, that
the three guiding principles of "one country, two systems", "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong", and High Degree of Autonomy
form the cornerstones of the Basic Law and are also the framework
within which the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR)
will conduct its affairs and which defines its relations with the
Central Authorities.
</P>
<P>
Suen said that People's Republic of China's constitution and
the Basic Law provide legal protection for the former colony's
capitalist system and way of life and that the leaders are
committed to these principles.
</P>
<P>
He quoted President Jiang Zemin as saying during the First
Session of the Ninth National People's Congress last month that
the central authorities and all provinces, regions, and
municipalities will abide by the Basic Law and fully support the
HKSAR government in accordance with the Basic Law.
</P>
<P>
The Central People's Government will not allow any authorities
on the mainland, or any local regions to interfere in matters
involving the autonomy of the HKSAR, he said, and that this
demonstrates the commitment of the government to the Basic Law and
to relations between the mainland and the HKSAR.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980404.0006 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Basic Law Means Hong Kong-Mainland Ties Entering New Era (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Suen said the Basic Law provides a broad principle for the
division of responsibilities between the Hong Kong SAR government
and the MFA Office. Since the founding of the HKSAR, the
Constitutional Affairs Bureau has maintained frequent contacts
with various departments in MFA and they have developed a smooth
and cordial working relationship, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong continues to play an active role in international
affairs and maintains close contacts with international
partners. Its government representatives have been part of
China's delegations in more than 30 international conferences and
have participated on their own under the name "Hong Kong, China",
in over 500 international conferences.
</P>
<P>
In addition, he said, the central government has agreed to give
authorization to the Hong Kong SAR government for 34 bilateral
agreements on air services, overflights, juridical assistance, and
visas.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, he said they are confident that cooperation with the
MFA will allow Hong Kong's external affairs to be handled properly
in line with the Basic Law and the 'one country, two systems'
principle.
</P>
<P>
Suen said that the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the
State Council has good contacts with the Hong Kong SAR and that
there are direct contacts across the border between police and
immigration and customs officers that contribute much to mutual
understanding and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
This represents the result of their determination to implement
the Basic Law and to enhance mutual understanding and
communication and he said he believes that the mainland and Hong
Kong will do even more in the 21st century through common efforts
and cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
