<HEADLINE> Major US Business School To Train Chinese Insurance Personnel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The University of Pennsylvania's
Wharton school of business, one of the top business schools in the
United States, plans to help train people for the insurance
business in China.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent issue of International Business Daily,
one of Wharton's deans spoke at an inaugural lecture on March 27
and discussed the Chinese insurance situation and the challenges
that Chinese companies should face.
</P>
<P>
Because this business is close to opening-up more, many
international companies are looking for a way to get started in it
in China, and that this is a big challenge for Chinese colleges.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
