<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Crosses Over 9000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The Dow Jones industrial average
crossed over the 9,000 mark for the first time Friday morning as
investors continue to be optimistic about the U.S. economic
situation.
</P>
<P>
At 10 A.M. on the New York Stock Exchange, the 30 blue chip
company benchmark index stood at 9,008.57, 21.93 points higher
than yesterday's record close of 8,986.64 after a 118.32 gain.
</P>
<P>
The Dow rose over 14 percent this year, exceeding expectations
of many analysts who predicted a single digit growth this year
following three years of gains of more than 20 percent.
</P>
<P>
The market has been bullish amid feelings that the country's
inflation is within check. The Federal Reserve decided on March 31
that interest rates remain unchanged at 5.5 percent set in March
last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
