<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, April 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- The United Nations special group responsible for the
inspection of Iraqi presidential sites has finished their mission
"successfully," head of the group Janayatha Dhanapala said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Dhanapala, commissioner of the U.N. special group of senior
diplomats and arms experts told reporters Friday morning that his
mission was finished. (Iraq-U.N. Inspections)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Eight hundred Iraqi prisoners of war (POWs) released
by Iran arrived at the border post of al-Mundhariya early Friday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Iraqi weekly newspaper al-Zawra said on Thursday that Iran
would set free 6,000 Iraqi prisoners of war in the biggest such
kind of release since 1990. (Iraq-Iran-POWs)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Commission, the European Union (EU)'s
executive body, on Friday approved a package of humanitarian aid
worth 86 million ECU (100 million U.S. dollars) for former
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The aid, which will be managed by the European Community
Humanitarian Office (ECHO), will mainly support the repatriated or
displaced persons and refugees. (EU-Yugoslavia-Aid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TOKYO -- Japan and Russia has agreed to promote joint efforts
in the field of space science.
</P>
<P>
A Japan-Russia space cooperation commission met Thursday in
Tokyo and decided that the two countries will discuss space
projects in detail and exchange opinions among experts ahead of a
second meeting next year. (Japan-Russia-Space)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- Leaders from 10 Asian countries and 15 European Union
(EU) member states opened the Second Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM2)
here Friday, aiming at closer cooperation between the two
continents.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony, British Prime Minister Tony
Blair, the current EU president, said Europe and Asia shared many
things in common and the ASEM forum could help enhance cooperation
between the two regions.
</P>
<P>
"Europe and Asia have a relationship, which day by day grows
more closely interrelated," Blair said, citing that exports from
the European Union to Asia in 1996 totaled 204 billion
U.S. dollars, more than that from the United States. (UK-ASEM)
</P>
</TEXT>
