<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Canada Enjoy Excellent Ties: Pak Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan's Minister of State for
Foreign Affairs Siddique Khan Kanju said here Friday that his
country and Canada enjoy excellent bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Kanju expressed the hope that the on-going visit to Pakistan by
Governor General of Canada Romeo Leblanc would further strengthen
these ties.
</P>
<P>
While meeting Canada's Secretary of State for Asia-Pacific
Raymond Chan, who is here accompanying Romeo Leblanc, Kanju said
significant initiatives were taken during the Canadian Prime
Minister's visit to Pakistan two years ago.
</P>
<P>
"Our Prime Minister will also be visiting Canada later this
year," he said, adding that "such visits provide the impetus to
further consolidation of bilateral ties."
</P>
<P>
He briefed Raymond Chan in detail about the Pak-India relations
and the foreign secretary-level talks between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Unless the core issue of Kashmir was addressed in an integrated
manner besides other issues, the process of dialogue would not
succeed, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the Kashmir issue had to be resolved in
accordance with the resolutions of the Security Council of the
United Nations.
</P>
<P>
Kanju also briefed his Canadian guest on the situation in
Afghanistan and the initiatives taken by the Pakistani government
to bring all Afghan factions within negotiating range.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, Raymond Chan said that Canada would urge both
India and Pakistan to seek a political solution of their problems
including the Kashmir issue.
</P>
<P>
He said Canada would be happy to assist in any way. The offer
of mediation made by the Canadian Prime Minister during his last
visit to Pakistan was still open, he added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed Canada's concern over the situation in Afghanistan
and said that it would continue to support U.N. efforts to resolve
the conflict.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Pakistan's Acting Speaker Muhammad Jaffar Iqbal held
a meeting here with members of the Canadian parliament Deepak
Obhrai, Real Menard, Nelson A. Riis and Elizabeth Kingston, who
are also accompanying the Governor General.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting the two sides discussed issues including
prospects of the Canadian investment in Pakistan and Pak-Canada
relations.
</P>
<P>
Governor General of Canada Romeo Leblanc arrived here earlier
Friday on a four-day official visit. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
