<DOCNO> XIE19980404.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-03 16:43 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pro-Israeli Soldier Wounded in Bombing in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A member of the pro-Israeli South
Lebanese Army (SLA) was wounded in a bomb explosion in south
Lebanon Friday, the official National News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place on a road at the Brashit village in
the west of a buffer zone occupied by Israel in south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon's resistance group Hezbollah has claimed responsibility
for the blast.
</P>
<P>
The Hezbollah is spearheading a guerrilla war against an
estimated 1,200 Israeli troops and their 2,500 SLA allies who are
occupying south Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Israel set up a so-called Security Zone in the region in 1985
to allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border attacks
by Muslim guerrillas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
