<HEADLINE> Turkish Chopper Crash Kills 2 Police Officers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Two police officers were killed in
a helicopter crash in Turkey's largest city of Istanbul on
Friday, according to the Anatolia News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Four other officers aboard suffered injuries and were taken to
a local hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
The chopper bumped against the roof of a vacant building in a
downtown district Friday afternoon shortly after taking off from
the Ataturk International Airport.
</P>
<P>
