<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urges More Efforts to Promote Asia-Europe Partnership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Addressing the afternoon session of the Second Asia-Europe
Meeting (ASEM2), Premier Zhu said that the ASEM mechanism is of
major importance to "summing up the successful experience gained
in Asia-Europe cooperation over the past two years."
</P>
<P>
"Positive changes of strategic significance have taken place in
the mutually beneficial cooperation and mutual relations between
the two continents of Asia and Europe," Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides have also made marked progress in the fields of
political consultations, economic and trade cooperation, cultural
exchanges and cooperation in international affairs, he noted.
</P>
<P>
"Practice has proved that ASEM has already played and will
continue to play a positive role in promoting the friendly and
mutually beneficial cooperation between Asia and Europe," Premier
Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
Forecasting the future of ASEM, Premier Zhu expressed the
desire of establishing "a new type of Asia-Europe partnership,"
envisaging the prospects of Asia-Europe cooperation in the 21st
century.
</P>
<P>
Putting forward some fresh initiatives aimed at strengthening
Asia-Europe relationship, the Chinese premier stressed that both
sides "should persist in giving top priority to our respective
advantages and open up various cooperation channels."
</P>
<P>
He also appealed for reducing trade barriers, enhancing
cooperation in both large enterprises and small companies,
relaxing restrictions on technical transfers and providing
developing countries with advanced technologies.
</P>
<P>
Premier Zhu proposed to hold an "Asia-Europe Scientific and
Technological Ministerial Meeting" to exchange views on issues of
mutual intertest and work out specific measures for the
development of scientific and technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
On ASEM political consultation and dialogue, he pointed out:
"differences should be handled properly in the spirit of
respecting each other, seeking common ground while putting aside
differences and making steady progress."
</P>
<P>
"We should cherish and develop the existing sound atmosphere
for and momentum of dialogue, replace confrontation with dialogue
and conflict with cooperation, and strives to find and expand the
converging points of common interests," Premier Zhu said.
</P>
<P>
"We must establish and develop a new type of cross-century
partnership so as to contribute to peace and development in Asia
and Europe and in the world at large," he added.
</P>
<P>
Early Friday, Premier Zhu held talks with German Chancellor
Helmut Kohl at the conference center to exchange views on
bilateral relations and other issues of common interest.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday afternoon, Premier Zhu attended the summit talks of
the participating 10 Asian countries to coordinate their stands on
the key issues of the ASEM2 conference, especially on the Asian
financial crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
