<HEADLINE> China to Set up Investment Promotion Center in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- China will set up a center for the
promotion of its investment, development and trade in Zambia to further
strengthen the economic and trade cooperation between China and
Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The protocol on the establishment of the Chinese center was signed
here Friday.
</P>
<P>
At the signing ceremony, Zambian Commerce, Trade and Industry
Minister Enock Kavindele said that the establishment of the center is
another important milestone in the economic cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Zambian government will provide all the necessary
support to ensue that the centre achieves its intended objectives.
</P>
<P>
The minister thanked the Chinese government for its continued
support in various spheres of Zambia's economic development.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Ambassador to Zambia Wang Yunxiang said at the ceremony
that following the setting up of the Sino-Zambia Mulungushi Textiles
and the opening of Bank of China (Zambia) last year, the establishment
of the centre is another important economic activity that China has
carried out in Zambia.
</P>
<P>
"This proves that the Chinese business community has enough
confidence in the economic and political environment of Zambia," Wang
said.
</P>
<P>
Up to now, there are more than 30 Chinese business entities doing
business in Zambia, and China was the third largest investor in Zambia in
1997, with a total agreed investment of 30 millions U.S. Dollars, said
the ambassador.
</P>
<P>
The Sino-Zambia trade volume increased by 140 percent last year,
with a total amount of 37.2 million dollars, said Wang.
</P>
<P>
The Lusaka-based center is responsible for promoting the import,
export, re-export, wholesale and retail of commodities, encouraging
Chinese enterprises to make investments in Zambia, promoting the joint
ventures activities among Chinese and Zambian enterprises and
providing all kinds of services to Chinese enterprises doing business
in Zambia. 
</P>
