Secretary-General will not dignify this remark with a reply."
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary-General said he is concerned at the level of
invective that is being used by some people in leadership
positions in Washington form whom one would expect better," Carlos
added.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief negotiated a deal with Iraqi President on February
23 which ended the crisis over UN weapons inspection in Iraq and
averted a possible U.S. military strike against Iraq. 
