<HEADLINE> ASEM Plans Follow-up Activities for Asia-Europe Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Leaders attending the second
Asia-Europe meeting here agreed Saturday on a number of follow-up
activities for strengthening Asia-Europe cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Following is a list of the activities:
</P>
<P>
-- Vision Group, set up at the ASEM 2, will hold its first
meeting in Cambridge on April 6, 1998, and will submit its report
to foreign ministers in 1999 then to ASEM 3 along with the
ministers' views on its recommendations;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold further Asia-Europe Young Leaders Symposia in
Baden/Vienna, Austria on May 24-29, 1998 and in South Korea in
1999 and Business Fora in Korea in 1999, in Austria in 2000 and in
Singapore in 2001;
</P>
<P>
-- Establish the Asia-Europe Center at the University of
Malaya, Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia, which is intended to be upgraded
to an Asia-Europe University;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold an Asia-Europe Small and Medium-sized Enterprise
conference in Naples on May 28-30, 1998;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold a meeting of experts of children's welfare in Britain
in October 1998;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold a meeting on protecting and promoting cultural heritage
in ASEM countries in Vietnam in autumn of 1998 to draft a relevant
plan of action for the effective implementation of this initiative
from 1999 onward;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold a seminar on the roles of the state and the market in
Copenhagen before the foreign ministers' meeting in 1999;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold a seminar of experts of health care in Vietnam in
autumn of 1998 to discuss Asia-Europe cooperation in combining
traditional and modern medicine and treatment for community health
care;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold the first Asia-Europe Forum of Governors of Cities
(AEFGC) in Thailand in 1999;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold a seminar on labor relations in The Hague in October
1998;
</P>
<P>
-- Hold a meeting of foreign, economic and finance ministers of
ASEM countries in Germany in 1999 before ASEM 3 to be held in
Seoul, South Korea, in 2000. 
</P>
