<HEADLINE> Rabbani Calls for End to Afghan Conflict </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Ousted Afghan president
Burhanuddin Rabbani said that the Afghan imbroglio could not be
resolved unless all the Afghans sit together and thrash out a
viable solution to the issue.
</P>
<P>
According to a report reaching here from the Afghan capital of
Kabul, Rabbani made the comment Saturday during his meeting with a
delegation of Muslim Hands (Charitable Organization) at his
ancestral village Faizabad in Badakhshan province.
</P>
<P>
"The history would not forgive us if we failed to establish
lasting peace in war-ravaged Afghanistan which had a direct
bearing on the future generation of the country," Rabbani was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Expressing deep regret over the ongoing blood shed in
Afghanistan, Rabbani said, "it is our moral obligation to save the
Afghan nation from total destruction."
</P>
<P>
He said that he has full regard and honor for all the leaders
of Afghanistan including the Taliban and he urged them to save
their generation from total collapse and disaster. 
</P>
