<HEADLINE> 3 Thais Killed in Car Accident in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Three Thai nationals were killed and
a fourth injured when their car overturned on its way from Cairo
to the Mediterranean city of Alamein, about 260 kilometers
northwest of Cairo, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
