<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEM Calls for Closer Asia-Europe Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The 25 leaders attending the second
Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM 2) agreed on Saturday to foster
political dialogue, reinforce cooperation in economic and other
fields.
</P>
<P>
By adopting the Chairman's Statement at the end of the two-day
conference, leaders from China, Japan, South Korea, the seven
ASEAN (Association of Southeast Asian Nations) countries, and the
15 EU member states, confirmed that the ASEM process should be
conducted on the basis of equal partnership, mutual respect and
mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
It should also be an open and evolutionary process conducted on
the basis of consensus by the heads of state and government.
</P>
<P>
"As an informal process, ASEM needs not be institutionalized. It
should stimulate and facilitate progress in other fora; go beyond
governments in order to promote dialogue and cooperation between
the business/private sectors of the two regions," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
At the summit, all leaders recognized the growing
interdependence of the economies and economic policies of the ASEM
countries and agreed on the importance of deepening dialogue and
cooperation between Asia and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the leaders looked forward to the early
implementation of the Investment Promotion Action Plan and of the
Trade Facilitation Action Plan, adopted at the ASEM, and asked
economic ministers of the ASEM countries to supervise the
implementation closely.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that it was essential in a highly integrated world
economy that all trading nations were members of the World Trade
Organization, and full participation in the WTO by ASEM partners
will strengthen the organization.
</P>
<P>
On the financial crisis in Asia, the leaders attached high
importance to remedying the financial and economic situation in
Asia and reaffirmed their commitment to working together to
address this global concern.
</P>
<P>
The leaders encouraged businesses to play an active part in the
restoration of economic confidence and growth in the affected
Asian countries, and to maintain and extend business investment
activities in both regions.
</P>
<P>
They also attached importance to the cooperation in the fields
of culture, science and technology in order to diversify further
Asian-European cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Since science and technology has increasingly become the key
factor and chief engine for economic growth, and there is enormous
potential for mutually-beneficial cooperation between Asia and
Europe, leaders noted various follow-up activities in this field
and called for further efforts to strengthen technological
cooperation between Asia and Europe," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also agreed to expand Asian-European dialogue on
global political issues and general security issues, such as
environment, arms control, illegal drugs and money laundering, and
the welfare of women and children.
</P>
<P>
The first ASEM meeting was held in Bangkok, Thailand, in 1996,
and the next ASEM conference will be held in Seoul, South Korea,
in the year 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980404.0065 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
