<HEADLINE> Fashionable Clothing Gains Popularity in Lhasa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Tibetan youngsters are quietly
abandoning traditional dress and opting instead for fashionable
clothing.
</P>
<P>
Young Tibetan women greet the arrival of Spring by changing
their rather redundant winter clothing for colorful fashionable
dress.
</P>
<P>
One particular street in Lhasa is particularly well-known for
shops selling the latest fashions, with 100 boutiques changing
their window displays almost overnight during the transition from
one season to another. Spring collections from coastal areas such
as Guangzhou appear in the shops almost immediately.
</P>
<P>
Shopping for fashionable clothing has emerged as a new hobby
for an increasing number of young Tibetan women, with related
items representing a new flash point for consumption.
</P>
<P>
The popularity of fashionable clothing in Lhasa readily
indicates that Tibetans share the pursuit of beauty on the same
level as other nationalities, according to a Tibetan fashion
designer.
</P>
<P>
Most urban residents no longer have to worry about adequate
food and clothing, and can thus pay greater to their quality of
life and indeed fashionable clothing.
</P>
<P>
Gaizhoin, a clerk for a government department, wears
fashionable dresses during her leisure time. She said that dresses
add to pleasantness and spark a more lively aura in certain social
activities.
</P>
<P>
She said that some fashionable clothing items cost as much as
1,000 yuan, but quickly added the expense is worthwhile since they
make her appear more vigorous and impressive.
</P>
<P>
Foresighted businessmen have paid special attention to the
clothing market in Tibet, with many opening shops to sell the
latest fashions. Various name brand products have gained
increasing popularity in Tibet.
</P>
<P>
One boutique owner who opened a shop in Lhasa some five years
ago said he never imagined that styles of fashionable clothing
would change so fast. He cited the intense competition and noted
risk in operating boutiques is greater than purchasing shares on
the stock market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
