<HEADLINE> HK Residents Urged to Be Actively Involved in Legislature Election </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong government
expressed its hope that the local residents will take an active
part in the May election so as to produce a credible and
representative Legislative Council.
</P>
<P>
Anson Chan, administrative secretary of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR), made the remarks at the opening
ceremony of an election carnival at noon Saturday.
</P>
<P>
She stressed the government's commitment to ensuring the
election will be conducted in a fair and open way and acceptable
to the Hong Kong people.
</P>
<P>
This election, the first of its kind since the Hong Kong SAR
was founded on July 1 last year, is of special significance, Chan
said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong citizens will choose their representatives to the
Legislative Council by casting their ballots, she said, adding
that the active involvement by both citizens and candidates in
the election marks an important step for practicing "Hong Kong
people governing Hong Kong".
</P>
<P>
She went on to say that the government will develop democracy
in accordance with the blueprint of the Basic Law and in a
gradual and progressive manner.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Chan noted, that the nomination of candidates for the
Legislative Council will begin on April 9.
</P>
<P>
She expressed the belief that more large-scale publicity
activities will be held before May 24 so as to let citizens know
more about the election arrangements.
</P>
<P>
She urged a total of 2.8 million registered voters to actively
cast their votes on May 24 and select their representatives to the
legislature.
</P>
<P>
The Legislative Council will be made up of 60 members with 20
returned from the geographical constituencies through direct
elections, 30 from the functional constituencies and 10 from the
800-strong Election Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
