<HEADLINE> UNHCR Repatriates 470 Somali Refugees to </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The voluntary repatriation of
Somali refugees administered by the United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) continued Friday with the
transport of 470 refugees to their destination and dispersal
point in Borama, a north-western Somaliland town, the Ethiopian
Herald reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This is the first batch of nearly 8,000 refugees to be
repatriated in two weeks from Darwanaji camp in eastern Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The new repatriation plan followed the successful pilot
voluntary repatriation of 10,000 Somali refugees last year from
the camps Teferiber, Hartisheik and Darwanaji in eastern Ethiopia
to areas between west of Hargeisa and Borama in Somaliland.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted David Jamieson, UNHCR assistant
representa- tive and program coordinator as saying that the
UNHCR's plan for this year is to repatriate some 60,000 Somali
refugees, out of the total of 286,000 in eastern Ethiopia back to
their homeland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
