<HEADLINE> Mozambique: Detained S. African Has Defense </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A defense attorney has been found
for the former South African foreign ministry director Robert
Mcbride who was detained in Maputo for alleged arms smuggling, the
Mozambican News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Albano Silva was asked to be a defense attorney for Robert
Mcbride, former foreign ministry department director for Asian
affairs who was detained on March 9 in southern Mozambique. the
report said.
</P>
<P>
Silva is believed to be one of the most distinguished lawyers
in Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, he was an 1977 graduate from the Law
Department of Eduard Mondlane University and earned his fame for
his successful defense in a well-known criminal suit involving 40
tons of hashish.
</P>
<P>
Silva said that he will do his best to find out the truth. He
said he did not know Mcbride, but he will soon arrange talks with
the defendant.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Mcbride's wife wants to be his defense
attorney, but she has been declined on the ground that she was
not registered with the association of attorneys in Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
Mcbride refused to speak without the presence of his attorney
after he was detained for suspected involvement in arms
smuggling. Now he is held in custody in the heavily-guarded
Machava prison in the suburb of Maputo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
