<HEADLINE> Uganda: Fresh Cholera Outbreak Claims 83 Lives </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kampala, April 4 (Xinhua)-- Fresh outbreak of cholera has
claimed 83 lives in eastern Uganda, the New Vision reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted Richard Othieno, the Mbale District
Director of Health Services, as blaming a religious sect for
blocking timely medical assistance from health institutions.
</P>
<P>
In one case, the sect whose name Othieno did not reveal hid
patients from the medical personnel patrolling Soono Parish of
the district.
</P>
<P>
Local administration police was forced to grab patients for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
But the sect later came back again and get the patients away.
Two patients died as a consequence, Othieno said.
</P>
<P>
But a source in Soono unveiled the sect as "Red Cross", which
believes in resurrection.
</P>
<P>
The source said the sect members pick up bodies of the dead,
hoping the deceased will resurrect later. 
</P>
</TEXT>
