<HEADLINE> Memorial Ceremony Honors Revolutionary Martyrs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Ten thousands of students from
more than 20 universities, middle and primary schools in Nanjing,
capital of east China's Jiangsu Province, joined in memorial
ceremonies held at the Yuhuatai Cemetery today to honor
revolutionary martyrs.
</P>
<P>
Yuhuatai is considered to be a sacred site for commemorating
participants in China's new democratic revolution and a base for
nationwide patriotic education.
