<HEADLINE> ASEM Meeting Ends with Adoption of Chairman's Statement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The second Asia-Europe meeting
closed here Saturday with the adoption of a chairman's statement.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference, participated by the leaders of 10 Asian
countries and EU's 15 member states plus president of the EU
commission, covered a wide range of political, economic and social
issues.
</P>
<P>
The leaders also agreed to set up an ASEM Trust Fund to provide
assistance to ASEM countries, primarily in assessing the poverty
impact of the financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
In his closing speech, British Prime Minister Tony Blair said
the conference was fruitful by working out two important
initiatives, the establishment of the ASEM Trust Fund at the World
Bank and the Center for Financial Restructuring which will be
invaluable in providing necessary technical expertise and in
addressing the impact on people affected by the current financial
difficulties.
</P>
<P>
"By working together, we can help our peoples both to cope and
to benefit from inevitable change" in the world, he said.
</P>
<P>
The first ASEM meeting was held in Bangkok, Thailand, in 1996,
and the next ASEM conference will be held in Seoul, South Korea,
in the year 2000. 
</P>
