<HEADLINE> Chinese Leaders Join Landscaping Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin and
a number of other Party and state leaders planted trees today as
part of an annual event which attracted over two million
Beijing residents and members of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army.
</P>
<P>
Leaders arrived at the Yuyuantan Park this morning to work
alongside dozens of elementary students.
</P>
<P>
"I used to visit Yuyuantan park quite often, but remarkable
changes have taken place since that time," said Jiang Zemin, who
was participating in the event for the ninth time since becoming
general secretary of the CPC Central Committee. "This is truly a
beautiful place," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"Every citizen has the obligation to plant trees and the Party
and State leaders should take the lead," said the jubilant Jiang
as he worked enthusiastically alongside the students.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng, chairman of the Standing Committee of National
People's Congress, participated in the activity prior to
discussions with senior officials on the Beijing Municipal Party
Committee.
</P>
<P>
