<HEADLINE> 16 Rebels Killed in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan troops killed at least
16 Tamil rebels Friday in the north and east of the country,
according to Military Spokesman Rp Witana Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the troops conducted an operation to destroy
a rebel camp around 2:00 a.m. Friday in Trincomalee district in
the east of the country.
</P>
<P>
After brief fighting rebels abandoned the camp and withdrew
into the jungle. At least six rebels were killed during the
operation and their bodies were recovered along with a very large
stock of food items and medicine.
</P>
<P>
The rebel camp was completely destroyed. However, three
soldiers were injured due to rebel fire and evacuated to
Trincomalee hospital for treatment, Witana said.
</P>
<P>
He said that on the same day in the southeast of Mankulam in
Northern province, troops observed a rebel movement and engaged
with small arms killing three rebels.
</P>
<P>
Another six rebels were killed Friday in the southeast of
Olumadu when troops sniped. On the same day, the troops killed
one Tiger and recovered some weapons in the southwest of
Karuppuktti in the north, said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-year war for a
separate state for the minority Tamils in the north and east of
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
