<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam's Literacy Rate Increases Nationwide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The national literacy rate in
Vietnam increased from 88 percent in 1990 to 92 percent in 1997,
thanks to the combined efforts of the whole nation, local media
reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The figure was released at a conference by the National
Literacy Committee reviewing the literacy and primary education
universalization between 1990-97 and discussing measures to
promote the work for 1998-2000.
</P>
<P>
Some 60 percent of provinces, 76.8 percent of districts and 86
percent of communes and wards nationwide have reached the national
standards of literacy and universal primary education, said the
report.
</P>
<P>
However, the report said that more efforts should be made in
the coming three years for localities, particularly the
mountainous areas, the Mekong delta and fishermen's villages, to
reach the nation's literacy standards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
