<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 10:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Saudis Beef up Disaster Prevention During Hajj </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The Saudi government has been
beefing up disaster-prevention measures as 2 million Muslim across
the world are heading for Mecca and packing the holy sites to pay
their homage to the Prophet.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Mecca, this year's hajj is marked by
huge efforts by the authorities to try to avoid a repeat of
previous disasters, which had caused heavy loss of lives.
</P>
<P>
Intricate preparations have been undertaken throughout the year
for the world's biggest gathering of the Muslims and "all
necessary facilities were set" for the hajj, which starts on April
6.
</P>
<P>
The reports said a total of 10,800 fire-resistant tents have
been fitted with 42,000 water sprinklers in a bid to avoid the
1997 blaze during the pilgrimage, which was caused by a cooking
gas cylinder in a camp on the Mina plain, south of Mecca, killed 343
pilgrims and injured many others.
</P>
<P>
Those tents provided this year cover 25 percent of the targeted
area in Mina and is the first phase of a plan to set up all the
tents of the same kind to house 2 million pilgrims every year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Saudi authorities said they would encourage the
pilgrims to buy fast food and would punish those who insisted on
cooking meals in the camp area.
</P>
<P>
Some 600 roaming trucks would sell more than a million fast
food meals, Saudi Undersecretary of State of the Commerce Ministry
Mohammed Hassen Qareb was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Other precautions included underground storage of 100,000 cubic
meters of water for the pilgrims.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Interior Minister Prince Nayef Bin Abdel-Aziz, also
chairman of the Supreme Hajj Committee, inspected the facilities
at Hajj sites of Mecca, Mina, Arafat and Muzdalifa as well as the
security arrangements recently and said "Saudi Arabia has made all
arrangements for the welfare and security of pilgrims."
</P>
<P>
The pilgrimage to Mecca, the birthplace of Prophet Mohammad, is
the largest annual event in the kingdom. According to Islamic
teachings, every Muslim should try to make the pilgrimage at least
once in a lifetime. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
