<HEADLINE> Nigeria Releases Mascot of '99 World Youth Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria Friday released the mascot
and slogan for the 10th World Youth Football Championship
scheduled for 1999 in the West Africa country.
</P>
<P>
The mascot, designed by Ayodeji Ajao from Ibadan City, was
chosen from over 420 entries, announced Abdulmumuni Aminu, the
executive chairman of the Nigeria '99 Local Organizing Committee,
in Abuja.
</P>
<P>
The mascot, named "Pego", is an eagle with stretched wings,
wearing a face cap and a medal with number 10 boldly inscribed on
it and "Nigeria '99" written on its chest.
</P>
<P>
Pego wears a pair of boots and socks and is kicking a football.
</P>
<P>
Eagle is both the symbol of Nigeria and the name of the
Nigerian national football team.
</P>
<P>
According to Aminu, who is also the chairman of the Nigeria
Football Association, Pego is an acronym for purposeful,
entertaining, gallantry and optimism, all features of Nigeria's
football culture and spirit of the tournament.
</P>
<P>
The slogan for Nigeria '99 is "The goal is friendship".
</P>
<P>
Both the mascot and slogan will be officially launched soon in
Abuja, the national capital, the official said. 
</P>
