<HEADLINE> Nigeria: 280 Die in Boat Mishap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, April 4 (Xinhua) -- No fewer than 280 passengers were
feared dead in a boat accident in Akwa Ibom state, southeastern
Nigeria, the Daily Times reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
However, 20 others survived the mishap in which goods worth
several millions of Naira were also saved.
</P>
<P>
The boat was said to have been rocked by violent waves in the
course of its voyage and capsized near a beach Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A combined team of divers, marine, police and immigration
officials are already on rescue mission in the sea to fish bodies
of the victims.
</P>
<P>
The state police has confirmed the accident and disclosed that
some of the bodies have been recovered. While efforts are
continuing to recover other bodies, the injured have been taken
to the hospital, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The state immigration department said Friday that it had begun
investigation into the accident, ostensibly to ascertain the
identities of the victims.
</P>
<P>
A similar accident in which 700 people died occurred last year
during a trip to Gabon, Cameroon and Equatorial Guinea. 
</P>
