<HEADLINE> Male Kindergarten Teachers Play Important Role (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ten years ago, Pan began to adopt such teaching methods as
imitation, consciousness and thought-provocation. He also started
courses in boxing, shooting, fencing and wrestling to improve the
students' courage through reasonable and rational pushing and
shoving.
</P>
<P>
"I don't expect my kid to be an excellent artist or a
first-class scientist," said one parent, an employee with China
Eastern Airlines. "But I hope he becomes a man with a strong will
and good habits."
</P>
<P>
Feng Lirong, president of the Soong Ching Ling Kindergarten
where Pan works, said: "The teaching methods adopted by Pan are
better compared with the traditional ones in that it make kids
more quick-witted, courageous and more capable of protecting
themselves."
</P>
<P>
Last year the school employed another male kindergarten
teacher, a graduate of Shanghai Jiaotong University. The new
teacher monitors science courses and is also very popular.
</P>
<P>
Male teachers encounter great difficulties from society because
taking care of children is traditionally regarded as "inferior
work" in China and only done by females.
</P>
<P>
Pan, 31, said he has courted women several times, and each time
was rebuffed because of his "inferior occupation."
</P>
<P>
"I have confidence and I will convince the public with my
achievements that a male teacher can build his career in
kindergarten," Pan said.
</P>
<P>
This autumn, Pan will tour Canada as a visiting scholar and
lecturer on his teaching methods. 
</P>
</TEXT>
