<HEADLINE> Vietnam, Ukraine Sign Protocol on Scientific Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and Ukraine has signed their
first protocol on science and technology cooperation, newspapers
here reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The protocol was signed Friday by Vietnam's Deputy Minister of
Science, Technology and Environment Chu Hao and his Ukrainian
counterpart B.V. Grinhev under the framework of an agreement the
two countries signed in 1996.
</P>
<P>
