<HEADLINE> New Cabinet Structure Agreed Upon in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Romania's prime minister nominee
Radu Vasile announced here Friday that parties in the country's
ruling coalition have agreed on the structure of a new cabinet.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, he said, positions for two ministers of
state and two ministerial representatives will be eliminated in
the new cabinet as compared with the one headed by former Prime
Minister Victor Ciorbea.
</P>
<P>
The new cabinet will be made up of a prime minister, a minister
of state to be filled by the defense minister and 23 ministers,
Vasile said.
</P>
<P>
Vasile, from the National Peasant's Party, the biggest in the
seven-party ruling coalition, was nominated for the prime
ministership last Wednesday, and was entrusted by President Emil
Constantinescu on April 2 to form a new cabinet within two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Talking to the press Friday, Vasile said he will push for a
sweeping structural reform in the cabinet so as to improve its
efficiency. For this purpose, he added, he will strive to prepare
a draft law and present it to the parliament for debate in
September. 
</P>
