<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Privatize Domestic Air Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- The domestic air services would be
given entirely to the private sector while the national Biman
Bangladesh Airlines will concentrate mainly on regional and
international routes, the Independent newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Civil Aviation and Tourism Minister
Mosharraf Hossain while on a recent visit to a private airline in
Dhaka.
</P>
<P>
The issue of allowing private sector airlines to operate on
regional routes "may be considered later on", the minister said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Biman incurs a loss of 200 million taka (about
4.35 million U.S. dollars) annually on its domestic routes.
</P>
<P>
"The loss is recovered from the income of its international
wing," he said, adding that Biman "will raise fare on its domestic
route from May next."
</P>
<P>
The government encouraged the private sector to come forward,
taking advantage of the atmosphere created for this purpose, he
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
