<HEADLINE> Vietnam Will Continue Open-Door Policy: Party Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam will continue its open-door
policy in the national renovation process, Vietnamese Communist
Party General-Secretary Le Kha Phieu said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to the World Affairs Weekly published Saturday, Phieu
reaffirmed the country's policy of befriending all nations "by
gradually opening its door and integrating itself into the region
and the world."
</P>
<P>
"In the present-day time, closing the door to industrialize and
modernize the country is an unrealistic solution or illusion,"
said the party chief.
</P>
<P>
However, he stressed the aim of the policy is for the
development. "We cannot undertake the door opening and integration
for the sake of the door opening and integration, we do it for the
development of the country," Phieu added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
