<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan Police Arrest Four People over Heroin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan police have arrested three
Tanzanians and one Kenyan who were found in possession of 1,150
grams of heroin, according to a Kenya Times report Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kenya Airports Police Unit Commandant Isaac Muthuuri was
quoted as saying Friday that the drugs had bean swallowed by the
four in form of sealed pellets.
</P>
<P>
The four, who were on transit in Tanzania to Tanga, had
boarded a Gulf Air flight from Tehran and were apprehended by
Kenyan customs police.
</P>
<P>
The three Tanzanians had carried 25 pellets, 38 pellets and 25
pellets respectively while the Kenyan carried 27 pellets,
Muthuuri confirmed.
</P>
<P>
He said that customs officials found 145 kilograms of bhang
stashed in a consignment from South Africa marked "spare parts"
on March 24.
</P>
<P>
Late last year, he added, another consignment marked "canned
food" from India turned out to be heroin.
</P>
<P>
Nairobi, capital of Kenya, has become one of transit centers
for drug traffickers in Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
