<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Four Killed in Philippine Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- A wayward van collided head-on with
a passenger jeep along a super highway south of Manila Friday
night, killing four people and seriously injuring 18 others,
police confirmed Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Police said a north-bound van rammed and crossed over the
center barrier of the south Luzon express way in Muntinlupa city,
Metro Manila, hitting the approaching south-bound jeep.
</P>
<P>
Three of the dead were aboard the van. Most of the injured, who
were rushed to a nearby hospital, were the jeep's passengers.
</P>
