<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 182 Killed in Bangladesh Road Accidents in 1st Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 4 (Xinhua) -- At least 182 people were killed in
69 road accidents in Bangladesh in the first three months of this
year, a police source said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Reckless driving, inefficiency of the drivers and lack of
public awareness are the main causes of the accidents, according
the source.
</P>
<P>
Overloading in transport also contributes to the frequency of
accidents, an official from the Bangladesh Road transport
Authority said.
</P>
<P>
The most tragic of the road accidents this year was the
collision between a passenger bus and a truck on the
Dhaka-Chittagong highway in Comilla, 90 km southeast of Dhaka, on
January 23. Ten people were killed and 40 others injured in the
accident.
</P>
<P>
Also on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway, two inter-district
passenger buses fell into a roadside ditch on March 28 due to
reckless driving, leaving nine people dead and at least 25
injured.
</P>
<P>
About 20 percent of the accidents during the three months
involved motor vehicles falling into roadside ditches due to
reckless driving. 
</P>
</TEXT>
