<HEADLINE> 34 Die as Bus Falls Into Ditch in Central India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 4 (Xinhua) -- At least 34 people, including 26
children and five women, were killed and 16 others seriously
injured Friday in a road accident in India's central State of
Madhya.
</P>
<P>
The Pioneer newspaper reported Saturday that the tragedy
occurred when a mini-bus fell into a 30-feet-deep ditch due to
brake failure near Delawadi Ghat, 60 km from Bhopal, capital of
Madhya.
</P>
<P>
In a message released Friday night, Indian Prime Minister Atal
Bihari Vajpayee expressed deep grief at the bus tragedy and his
concern at such accidents taking place frequently in the country.
 
</P>
