<HEADLINE> Vasco Beats Guadalajara in Libertadores Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Luizao scored two
goals to pace Vasco to sail into the next round of Libertadores
Cup here Friday night.
</P>
<P>
In a scoreless first half, Luizao tasted his first kick against
Mexico's Guadalajara goalie Zedano as the ball flew high over the
post.
</P>
<P>
Vasco blew another chance in the 40th minute when a free kick
by Pedrinho smashed into the goal post.
</P>
<P>
In the second half, both teams kept each other locked up until
Guadalajara's Robles was expelled in the 56th minute, but Ramon
sent another free kick to the post four minutes later.
</P>
<P>
All that changed when Luizao headed in a goal in the 68th
minute before Vasco mounted a series of good plays.
</P>
<P>
In the 80th minute, Luizao put a great dribble to Ramon and
recovered the ball off the hands of goalie Zedano to net in his
second.
</P>
<P>
The loss eliminated Guadalajara from the next round as it
tailed in the group that also included Gremio and Mexico's
America. 
</P>
</TEXT>
