<DOCNO> XIE19980404.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poll: Most Americans Feel Influenced by Martin Luther King Jr. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A new poll by the Marist
Institute says most Americans feel the late Martin Luther King Jr.
has influenced their lives.
</P>
<P>
The survey says that 30 years after the civil rights leader was
killed in Memphis, Tennessee, 58 percent of the country feels his
life influenced them somewhat or a great deal.
</P>
<P>
The feeling was stronger among black Americans at 89 percent.
</P>
<P>
While 45 percent of white Americans said King influenced them
little or not at all, only 11 percent of blacks felt that way.
</P>
<P>
The responses were reversed when it came to the course of race
relations in the United States. Sixty-two percent of whites said
they thought race relations had improved in the years since King
was assassinated, compared to only 40 percent of blacks.
</P>
<P>
The poll found that 63 percent of blacks thought the progress
towards civil rights for minorities was too slow, while half of
whites thought the pace had been about right. Thirteen percent of
whites and three percent of blacks thought the pace was too fast.
</P>
<P>
The telephone survey was conducted on January 26 and 27, among
917 adults within the continental United States. Phone numbers
were selected to ensure that each region of the country was
represented in proportion to its population.
</P>
<P>
The pollsters say the survey has a margin of error of 3.5
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980404.0166 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Leaders Call for Closer Ties with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of the Communist Party of
Vietnam (CPV) called for closer relations with the Communist Party
of China (CPC) at meetings with a visiting CPC delegation Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese delegation is headed by Zeng Qinghong, alternate
member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and
member of the Secretariat of the Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
In their separate meetings with Zeng, General Secretary of the
CPV Central Committee Le Kha Phieu and Consultant of the Central
Committee Do Muoi urged more contacts and mutual support between
the two parties, underscoring the need for the two sides to draw
on each other's successful experience in the new era.
</P>
<P>
Noting the long-standing friendship between the two parties and
two nations, the CPV leaders praised the rapid development of
inter-party and bilateral ties in various fields since the
normalization of Sino-Vietnamese relations in 1991.
</P>
<P>
They said that the CPV and Vietnamese people were happy for the
achievements made by the CPC and Chinese people in their reforms,
opening to the outside world and socialist modernization.
</P>
<P>
The achievements were good not only for China, but also for the
world, they said.
</P>
<P>
Le Kha Phieu and Do Muoi stressed the CPV's policy to adhere to
the socialist road and its strategy to implement overall reforms,
adding that the party was determined to overcome all difficulties
in the bid to fundamentally industrialize and modernize the
country by 2020, as targeted by the CPV's eighth congress.
</P>
<P>
During the meetings, Zeng praised the overall reform led by the
CPV.
</P>
<P>
He said that Vietnam enjoyed political and social stability,
economic growth, continual improvement of people's lives and
marked progress in every field.
</P>
<P>
Zeng especially praised the smooth power transition completed
at the fourth plenary session of the CPV's eighth congress last
December and the National Assembly last September.
</P>
<P>
He said that the three visits to China by Do Muoi made a
significant contribution to promoting the friendly cooperation
between the two parties and two countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that both the CPC and the CPV upheld the combination of
the basic theories of Maxism and Leninism with the specific
practice. Both parties formulated their targets, policies and
guiding principles on the basis of their specific national
conditions, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zeng called for an increase of exchange and cooperation between
the two countries and expressed confidence that the two parties
and two peoples would achieve their respective goals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
