<DOCNO> XIE19980404.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Strengthens Supervision Over Administration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, April 4 (Xinhua) -- Officials including the
city's Party secretary and the Mayor, have to offer a detailed plan
to the local newspaper and get it published if they are scheduled
to move into state-funded new housing.
</P>
<P>
If the general public believes that the reasons listed in the
plan are not justifiable, then the plan could not be carried out.
</P>
<P>
Today's People's Daily reported that the new system,
implemented in Jinhua city, eastern China's Zhejiang Province,
aims to increase the transparency of government affairs and
prevent behind-the-scenes deals.
</P>
<P>
"The practice is virtually in line with the central
government's principle of 'rule by law', " said Qiu Baoxing,
secretary of the Communist Party Committee of the city.
</P>
<P>
He believed that making government affairs known to the public
could effectively reduce the possibilities of power-abusing and
check power-for-money deals.
</P>
<P>
To date, the system mainly covers a series of issues which the
public concerns most, such as the enrollment of students and
public servants, the registration of industrial and commercial
enterprises, the transfer and approval of the ownership of land.
</P>
<P>
By "devaluing power," namely only regards the power as a means
to serve the people, government officials can really become
"public servants," according to the Party secretary.
</P>
<P>
A total of five directors of the municipal government
departments have been dismissed, demoted or criticized publicly
for failing to implement the system.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that over 80 percent of city's villages have
also adopted the practice by publishing revenues and expenditures
of the villages on the notice boards, which has helped dispel the
doubts of the villagers.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Shangjin, mayor of the city, said that the practice has
closed the ties between government officials and ordinary citizens
and helped establish a clean and honest government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
