<HEADLINE> Frankie Liles Retains WBA Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Frankie Liles retained his WBA
super middleweight title by winning a unanimous decision over
Russian Andrei Schkalikov in Bayamon, Puerto Rico on Friday night.
</P>
<P>
Schkalikov took an aggressive manner, hurting Liles in both the
third and 10th rounds. Yet, two of the three judges scored the
bout 115-114 and the other saw it 118-110, all in Liles' favor.
</P>
<P>
Liles improved to 32-1 with 20 knockouts, while Schkalikov fell
to 29-4-1.
</P>
<P>
On the undercard, last-minute replacement Fred Norwood who had
29-0 including 18 knockouts, scored a unanimous decision win over
Venezuela's Antonio Cermeno to take the vacant WBA featherweight
title.
</P>
<P>
Cermeno, 26-2 with 16 knockouts, originally was to challenge
Puerto Rico's Wilfredo Vasquez, but Vasquez abandoned the WBA belt
to fight Prince Naseem Hamed for the WBO featherweight title on
April 18 in Manchester, England.
</P>
<P>
In an exciting bout, Colombia's Jorge Eliecer Julio (38-1)
stopped Daniel Cobra Jimenez at 2:26 of the ninth round to retain
his WBO bantamweight title.
</P>
<P>
Puerto Rico's Felix Trinidad, 32-0 with 28 knockouts, defended
his IBF welterweight title later Friday against Zairian challenger
Mahenge Zulu, 17-2 with 7 knockouts, at Bayamon's Ruben Rodriguez
Coliseum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
