<HEADLINE> Motor Vehicle Sales Up in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- A total of 37,500
automobiles were sold in Colombia during the first quarter of the
year, up by 24 percent compared with the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
About 13,300 motor vehicles were sold in March, more than half
for private use, said reports quoting data provided local
companies.
</P>
<P>
It had been estimated that about 145,000 vehicles would be sold
this year in Colombia. But experts here say the figure could go up
to 160,000 thanks to the positive sales performance in the first
quarter. 
</P>
