<HEADLINE> China Sees Steady Growth of Investment in Secondary Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China invested 73.2 billion yuan
in its industrial sectors in 1997, a year-on-year increase of 6.1
percent, according to the latest figures from the State Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Investment in Energy was 35.7 billion yuan, up 21.7 percent, and
nine billion yuan was earmarked for the machinery and electronics
sector, an increase of 4.2 percent over that of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The country also poured 1.7 billion yuan in its construction
sector, up 22.7 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
