<HEADLINE> China's Investment in Tertiary Industry Up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's investment in its tertiary
industry last year reached 108.2 billion yuan, up 13 percent over
that of 1996, according to the latest statistics from the State
Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, 32.8 billion yuan was put in the transportation,
postal and telecommunications services, up 32.8 percent, and 41.6
yuan was invested in real estate, public and consultancy services,
with a 3.7 percent growth over that of 1996. 
</P>
