Europe a major event in Sino-European relations.
</P>
<P>
Sant said the fact that Zhu chose Europe to start his first
overseas visit since he was elected premier showed the great
importance that China attached to the continent.
</P>
<P>
The prime minister made the remarks while meeting with Zu
Qinshun, the new Chinese ambassador to Malta, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Sant hoped Zhu's visit to Britain and France would be a great
success.
</P>
<P>
Since the two countries established diplomatic ties in 1972,
friendship and cooperation between the two nations have been
consolidating and developing, Sant said.
</P>
<P>
China always pursued peaceful foreign policies and maintained
that all countries, big or small, should be treated on an equal
basis. China respected the sovereignty and independence of Malta as
well as its foreign policies, the prime minister said.
</P>
<P>
The two sides shared common views on many regional issues in
Europe and the Mediterranean as well as on the development rights
of developing countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Sant also noted that his country was willing to further develop
the full, lasting and friendly cooperative ties with China.
