<HEADLINE> Defending Champions Khan, Martin Breeze into Semi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Jansher Khan of Parkistan advanced
to the semifinals at the British Open squash championships in
Birmingham, England, on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Jansher, six times champion, beat the pains in his knees to
eliminate unseeded Paul Johnson of England 15-11, 15-11, 17-15.
</P>
<P>
Jansher has the bright propect for the final as he will face
10th seed Australian Dan Jenson in the semifinal, a surprise
survivor over David Evans of Wales 9-15, 15-11, 15-6, 15-8.
</P>
<P>
Top seed Peter Nicol of Scotland stormed past British national
champion Simon Parke 15-13, 15-13, 15-6 to earn himself a chance
to play against world champion Rodney Eyles in semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Eyles, the fourth seed, edged over Australian compatriot John
White 17-16, 17-16, 15-12.
</P>
<P>
Women's defending champion Michelle Martin, aiming for her
sixth successive British Open title, breezed through compatriot
Carol Owens 9-5, 9-6, 9-2.
</P>
<P>
Australian Sarah Fitz-Gerald, world champion and top seed but
never winner of the British Open, routed England's Fiona Geaves, a
semifinalist last year, even more convincingly 9-1, 9-6 ,9-5,
</P>
<P>
Fourth-seeded Cassie Jackman of England also entered the last
four after beating German sixth seed Sabine Schoene 10-8, 9-6,
9-7. 
