<HEADLINE> China's Cement Production Up in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 4 (Xinhua) -- China's cement output amounted to
492.6 million tons in 1997, up 5.13 percent form the previous
year, according to the latest statistics from the State Statistics
Bureau.
</P>
<P>
East China's Shangdong province became China's largest cement
production center last year, with an annual output of 55.4 million
tons, an increase of 6.43 percent over 1996.
</P>
<P>
The other two major cement production centers are Guangdong and
Jiangsu province, with an output of 48.6 million tons and 38.8
million tons, respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
