<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Colombia Loses 12 Million Banana Boxes Due to "El Nino" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, April 3 (Xinhua) -- About 12 million boxes
of bananas were lost in Colombia due to the weather changes caused
by the "El Nino" climate phenomenon, a Colombian official said
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The weather phenomenon ruined 60,000 hectares of banana
plantations, Fernando Devis Morales, president of the Banana
Producers Association, said.
</P>
<P>
"Investments will be very costly, especially in the resowing,
because there are areas which have to be replanted," he said
</P>
<P>
Morales estimated that the producers will have to invest 10
million U.S. dollars to recover from the damage. 
</P>
</TEXT>
