<HEADLINE> U.S. Resumes Summer Time on Sunday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Most of the United States returns
to daylight saving time on Sunday when clocks go forward one hour
at 2 a.m. in each time zone.
</P>
<P>
The resumption will not be applied to Arizona, Hawaii, the part
of Indiana in the eastern time zone, Puerto Rico, the U.S. Virgin
Islands and American Samoa, which remain on standard time all the
year.
</P>
<P>
Daylight time is practiced from the first Sunday in April until
the last Sunday in October. 
</P>
