<HEADLINE> IFC Launches HK Dollar Global Medium-Term Notes Offering </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) announced Friday the launching of a 300 million
Hong Kong dollar issue which is equivalent to 38.7 million U.S.
dollars under its Global Medium Term Note program.
</P>
<P>
The 2-year notes, launched on April 1, carry a quarterly coupon
of 8.18 percent per annum and an issue price of 99.67 percent.
</P>
<P>
The proceeds of the issue will be swapped into US dollars
floating rate funds.
</P>
<P>
The joint lead managers are Hang Seng Bank and Societe Generale
Asia Limited.
</P>
<P>
The latest transaction brings IFC's market borrowing to about
3,755 million U.S. dollars for the fiscal year 1998 which started
on July 1, 1997.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and also the largest
multilateral source of financing for private sector projects in
developing countries. 
