<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Urges Europe to Help Address Asian Financial Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan on Friday urged European countries to adopt strong and
concrete measures to help Asian countries overcome the financial
crisis.
</P>
<P>
At a press conference held in London during the ASEM
conference, Tang said it is always easy to adopt a document but
it's more important to implement it and adopt strong measures to
translate ideas into reality.
</P>
<P>
Leaders from all the 25 participating members of the ASEM
meeting on Friday issued a special statement on the Asian
financial crisis, reaffirming the urgent need to respond
decisively to the crisis.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister said the impact of the financial
crisis in Asia has gone far beyond the Asian area, and has spread
to other regions of the world.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, all Asian countries, including those present at the
ASEM meeting, hope European countries to pay close attention to
this matter and make substantial contribution to alleviating the
financial problem.
</P>
<P>
"We think the European countries should be interested in this
matter and should make contributions, because by doing so, not
only the Asian countries will benefit, but Europe as well."
</P>
<P>
Tang pledged again not to devalue the Chinese currency. "The
message to Hong Kong is that we are determined to maintain
prosperity and stability in Hong Kong. The message to our Asian
neighbors is that China is a responsible country."
</P>
<P>
"We know that once we commit ourselves to this promise, we are
under pressure and we may pay a price. But in order to safeguard
the economic and financial stability in the Asian countries hit by
the financial crisis, we are willing to do so at any cost."
</P>
<P>
On China's accession into the World Trade Organization (WTO),
Tang said it is well acknowledged that China and the WTO need each
other. "On the one hand, China needs the WTO, but on the other
hand, the WTO is not a real world trading organization without the
participation of China."
</P>
<P>
He stated that over the past 12 years, China has been working
hard for its admission to the WTO, and has conducted numerous
negotiations on this issue. "The core of this issue is how to
strike a balance between rights and obligations. "
</P>
<P>
No matter when China will join the WTO, China's opening up
policy will not change and China will open wider to the outside,
he underlined.
</P>
<P>
On China's relations with Britain and the EU as a whole, Tang
said the official visit of Premier Zhu Rongji to Britain and the
China-European Union (EU) summit held on the sidelines of the ASEM
conference were very successful.
</P>
<P>
"As a result, the relationship between China and Britain as
well as the relationship between China and the EU will be brought
to a higher level."
</P>
<P>
Tang added that the main purposes of Zhu's visit to Britain and
his participation in the ASEM conference are to deepen mutual
understanding, to expand common ground and to promote mutual
cooperation and common development. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
