<HEADLINE> Lewinsky Lawyer Urges Probe End </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 3 (Xinhua) -- With Paula Jones' lawsuit
dismissed, former White House intern Monica Lewinsky's lawyer
pleaded publicly Friday with Whitewater prosecutors to end their
criminal investigation of his client.
</P>
<P>
"The American people want this matter to end," William Ginsburg
said.
</P>
<P>
Ginsburg said the effect of the judge's decisions to exclude
Ms. Lewinsky from the Jones case, and then to throw out the
lawsuit in its entirety is that the court "has ruled twice now
that there was no perjury," according to news reports.
</P>
<P>
Continued investigation of the matter will "be against the will
of the American people," he said.
</P>
<P>
However, Whitewater prosecutor Kenneth Starr has made clear the
judge's ruling will have no effect on his investigation into
whether President Bill Clinton and Ms. Lewinsky had an affair and
then lied about it under oath in the Jones case.
</P>
<P>
Ginsburg said that Starr needs to consider the will of the
country along with the facts and law. 
</P>
</TEXT>
